**Abstract:**
A brief working note titled "Christianity is Not a Doctrine" quoting Kierkegaard on the difference between faith and opinion/belief. Develops the argument that if Christianity were a doctrine it could be assented to or disbelieved, but one cannot fear a doctrine. Even demons, who have no "faith," are afraid of God - showing that faith involves existential engagement, not mere intellectual assent.

**AI Recommendation:** Fragment developing the faith-as-practical-engagement theme; connects to larger Chantilly project.

